        beaconDB
      </h1>
      <p class="lead mt-2">publicly sourced, publicly licensed</p>
      <p class="font-semibold">
        an in-development wireless geolocation database with public domain data
        dumps
      </p>
    </header>

    <img class="max-w-7xl w-full mx-auto" src="/plot.avif" />

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl prose prose-neutral prose-invert">
      <ul>
        <li><b>ethically sourced</b>: opt-in only data collection</li>
        <li><b>privacy friendly</b>: access point identifiers are hashed</li>
        <li>
          <b>abuse resistant</b>: updating existing data requires information
          only available in physical range of a beacon
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        beaconDB is currently
        <a href="https://github.com/beacondb/beacondb">in development</a>
        and not yet accepting data. however, you can still start collecting nearby
        networks now to upload later. beaconDB plans to support importing data from:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://github.com/christianrowlands/android-network-survey"
            >Network Survey</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://github.com/mjaakko/NeoStumbler">NeoStumbler</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://github.com/wiglenet/wigle-wifi-wardriving">WiGLE</a> -
          only networks you have collected
        </li>
        <li>
          wifi network beacon frames <a href="https://www.tcpdump.org/"
            >captured in PCAP-NG format</a
          > along with separate GPX tracks
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
